-- Key facts about Zynga
-- 
-- Fri Jul 1, 2011 2:13pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/07/01/us-factbox-factbox-idUSTRE7604BT20110701

 

 BANGALORE  (Reuters) - Zynga filed on Friday for an initial public offering of up to $1 billion, the latest in a series of hot social media companies to seek capital in the U.S. public markets. 

 Here are a few facts about the company, the top game publisher on Facebook: - Zynga was named after company founder Mark Pincus' American bulldog, Zinga. - The name Zinga is a nod to a legendary African warrior queen. - Peter Thiel, an investor in Zynga, was the co-founder of PayPal. He was also one of the earliest investors in Facebook and currently sits on its board of directors. - Zynga is the world's largest social game developer with more than 250 million monthly active users. - Zynga's games collectively have 232 million active monthly users, and 60 million daily active users. - Zynga's popular games include FarmVille, Mafia Wars. - Zynga is the fourth company to be founded by Mark Pincus. Pincus also started social-networking site Tribe.net, software company SupportSoft, which eventually went public, and FreeLoader, his first company, which opened in 1995. - Jeffrey Katzenberg, CEO of DreamWorks Animation, sits on the Zynga board. (Compiled by Brenton Cordeiro and Tanya Agrawal in Bangalore; Editing by Sriraj Kalluvila)